headline: ICE Treasury Clearinghouse Launch Deepens Role In Core Market Plumbing
summary: Intercontinental Exchange (NYSE:ICE) has received SEC approval for a new U.S. Treasury clearinghouse. The clearinghouse is now live, creating a rival in a roughly $30 trillion market that previously had a single major provider. ICE plans to extend clearing to repurchase agreements tied to Treasuries by the end of the year. For you as an investor, this move puts ICE deeper into the core plumbing of the U.S. financial system, alongside its existing exchanges, data services and clearing...

headline: Data Companies Hit by AI Selloff Push Back on Claude Threat
summary: Two of the companies battered by this week’s artificial-intelligence selloff, Thomson Reuters and Intercontinental Exchange, argued Thursday their valuable troves of proprietary data will shield them from AI disruption.  The legal-research business of Thomson Reuters can’t be easily replaced by AI companies that lack the company’s “unique and high-quality content” and “deep subject-matter expertise,” Chief Executive Stephen Hasker told analysts on an earnings call.  “General-purpose models cannot meet this standard,” Hasker said, speaking two days after a 16% drop in Thomson Reuters stock.

headline: Intercontinental Exchange (NYSE:ICE) Reports Upbeat Q4 CY2025
summary: Global market infrastructure company Intercontinental Exchange (NYSE:ICE) reported Q4 CY2025 results beating Wall Street’s revenue expectations, with sales up 35.3% year on year to $3.14 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.71 per share was 2.2% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
